r were “lost souls,” troubled, vulnerable girls with no one to care about them, or come looking if they disappeared.  The police think they’re runaways, but Kristi senses there’s something that links them, so Kristi decides to enroll, following their same steps.  There are whispers of a dark cult on campus whose members wear vials of blood around their necks and meet in secret chambers, rituals to which only the elite have access.  To find the truth, Kristi will need to become part of the cult’s inner circle, learn their secrets, and play the part of lost soul without losing herself in the process.  And the deeper she goes the more Kristi begins to wonder if she is hunter or the prey.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Brought to you by TriCom Podcast, dedicated to putting Authors In Your&lt;br /&gt;Pocket (tm)...http://www.authorsinyourpocket.com&lt;div class="blogger-post-footer"&gt;&lt;img width='1' height='1' src='https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/tracker/25687395-2833350629144558236?l=aiyp-enhanced.blogspot.com' alt='' /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/aiyp-enhanced/~4/-9-_yPzZrDc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description><thr:total xmlns:thr="http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0">0</thr:total><media:content url="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/aiyp-enhanced/~5/s9DePrz7Oyg/aiyp021108e.m4a" fileSize="12972681" type="audio/mpeg" /><itunes:explicit>no</itunes:explicit><itunes:subtitle>Featuring Lisa Jackson, #1 New York Times Best-selling Author, discussing her new latest novel LOST SOULS, her most harrowing novel yet… as a young woman’s determined hunt for a serial killer draws her into a twisted psychopath’s unspeakable crimes… LOST </itunes:subtitle><itunes:author>TriCom Podcast</itunes:author><itunes:summary>Featuring Lisa Jackson, #1 New York Times Best-selling Author, discussing her new latest novel LOST SOULS, her most harrowing novel yet… as a young woman’s determined hunt for a serial killer draws her into a twisted psychopath’s unspeakable crimes… LOST SOULS reunites Jackson with Detective Reuben Montoya and returns to the familiar backdrop of New Orleans. Jackson also re-introduces readers to now twenty-seven-year-old Kristi Bentz, a woman who has nearly died twice at the hands of a serial killer, and lived to tell about it. Her dad—and Montoya’s partner—New Orleans detective, Rick Bentz wants Kristi to stay out of danger, but if anything, Kristi’s experiences have made her even more fascinated by the mind of a killer, and she’s determined to become a true crime writer. Kristi seems to find her perfect subject after discovering that four girls have disappeared at All Saints College in less than two years. All four were “lost souls,” troubled, vulnerable girls with no one to care about them, or come looking if they disappeared. The police think they’re runaways, but Kristi senses there’s something that links them, so Kristi decides to enroll, following their same steps. There are whispers of a dark cult on campus whose members wear vials of blood around their necks and meet in secret chambers, rituals to which only the elite have access. To find the truth, Kristi will need to become part of the cult’s inner circle, learn their secrets, and play the part of lost soul without losing herself in the process. And the deeper she goes the more Kristi begins to wonder if she is hunter or the prey. Brought to you by TriCom Podcast, dedicated to putting Authors In Your Pocket (tm)...http://www.authorsinyourpocket.com</itunes:summary><itunes:keywords>authors,books,book,author,bookclub,interview,Publishing,TriCom,Literature,graphically,enchanced,Lisa,Jackson,James,Rollins,Nick,Adams,Evie,Rhodes,Michael,Eric,Dyson,George,Elliott,Clarke,Meg,Cabot,Pamela,J,Bailey,The,Good,Book,Club,Go</itunes:keywords><feedburner:origLink>http://aiyp-enhanced.blogspot.com/2008/02/authors-in-your-pocket-show-021108-lisa.html</feedburner:origLink><enclosure url="http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/aiyp-enhanced/~5/s9DePrz7Oyg/aiyp021108e.m4a" length="12972681" type="audio/mpeg" /><feedburner:origEnclosureLink>http://www.tricompodcast.com/pods/aiyp021108e.m4a</feedburner:origEnclosureLink></item><item><title>Authors In Your Pocket Show 12/17/07 Carl Weber, Something On The Side (Graphically Enhanced)</title><link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/aiyp-enhanced/~3/di_7P2-Uypw/authors-in-your-pocket-show-121707-carl.html</link><author>info@tricompodcast.com (TriCom Podcast)</author><pubDate>Mon, 17 Dec 2007 00:22:30 PST</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-25687395.post-8634703915267550051</guid><description>Featuring NYT bestselling author Carl Weber discussing his scandalously spirited new novel SOMETHING ON THE SIDE. Weber introduces readers to the bodacious women of the Big Girls Book Club (BGBC) Tammy, Egypt, Isis, Nikki, Coco, and Tiny.  There’s only one rule to be a member of this club, you must be at least a size 14 to join.  At the center of the club is president, Tammy.  She loves everything about her life— her family, her friends, but most of all she’d do anything for her husband Tim.  So much so, that for his birthday, she’s convinced that involving her best friend Egypt in a threesome with them would be the perfect gift, now if she could just convince Egypt.   Isis and her boyfriend, Tony, seem to have the perfect relationship — that is until a man from her past steps back into her life with only one goal in mind, to win back the woman he’s has never been able to forget.  Single mom Nikki isn’t so lucky with men.  After loving the father of her soon for so long, all she wants to do now is kill  him, especially since he can’t seem to stop disappointing their son every chance he gets—and then making her look like the bad guy.  Last but certainly not least, there’s hot-to-trot Coco Brown, who has a habit of messing around with married men. It doesn’t bother her, as long as they don’t try to deny it.  IN STORES JANUARY 29, 2008!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Brought to you by